column5: I finally have to do it, thanks to all with their generosity/ experience as to catching chromies. So in return I will give you my honey holes that produce fish. Good luck and enjoy
Thats one in a life time shot. That is very cool.
just wait and see my friend
I think I've been to that spot before.  The fishing sucks there..
was I with you that day or does that one stick around? I know I have, in fact I think I was there most of the long weekend...
That's beautiful Roy!!! Think that's what that beauty largemouth I lost on Friday was trying to signal towards me!
I know that spot lol  how far was it again i forget lol  Nice one Vince

just for you bud, head due east, when you see water continue on about 10 miles. Turn for due north and aim towards the cn tower. Keep your speed at 40mph, when the boat hits shoreline your there There are plenty of fish there to catch
